# Mojo and pixi in this repo

The `mojo` binary lives in the **pixi** environment. A bare shell often has **no `mojo` on PATH**, so do not suggest or run `mojo ...` without pixi.

**Prefer these patterns from the repo root:**

| Goal | Command |
|------|---------|
| Run a `.mojo` file (interpreter) | `pixi run mojo run path/to/file.mojo` |
| Build then run a binary (uses `MOJO_DEBUG_COMPILE_FLAGS`, runs `configure`) | `pixi run test path/to/file.mojo` |
| Build only | `pixi run build path/to/file.mojo` |
| Format | `pixi run format` |

When verifying compilation or executing demos/tests, **run the command yourself** with `pixi run ...` as above, not plain `mojo`.
